Effect of HLU on body weight, organ weight
The body weight of male control rats was significantly (
p
 < 0.05) greater than the body weight of female control rats (Fig. 
1
). Similarly, male HLU rats were heavier than female HLU rats (Fig. 
1
). To account for this variability in body weight while allowing for comparison between sexes, organ weights (heart, kidney, pancreas, spleen, uterus) were normalized to individual tibia length values that more accurately reflect physiological changes in organ weights
14
. Body composition analysis revealed no differences in total fat mass between study groups, however, control unexposed males had greater lean mass compared with control females (Fig. 
1
). Exposure to HLU reduced lean mass in males (Fig. 
1C
). Lean-to-fat mass ratio was not different between study groups (Fig. 
1
). Within each sex, HLU treatment did not affect organ weights (Fig. 
1
) except the hearts where male rats exposed to HLU had lower heart weight compared to the male control group (Fig. 
1
). HLU did not affect uterine weight in female SD rats (Fig. 
1
).
